Orchestrates a summarization run over an abstract `Fs` + `Agent`: writes leaf `.ctx` files for source targets, then walks affected directories leaf-up (deepest first, repo root last) writing `rollup.ctx`. `intent.md` is read as rollup input but never written by this file.

Entry points: `load_prompts(fs, prompts_dir)` reads `summarizer-leaf.md` and `summarizer-rollup.md`, erroring with `SummError::MissingPrompt` if either is missing. `run(fs, agent, prompts_dir, targets, progress)` loads prompts then delegates to `run_with_prompts`, which is the real driver and is exposed separately so callers can load prompts from a different root than the tree being summarized (e.g. process cwd vs. scan root). `summarize_leaf` and `summarize_rollup` do one unit each and return the `.ctx` path written.

Access control: `summarize_leaf` calls `ctx_core::access::deny_reason(src, fs.is_ignored(src)?)` before reading — gated/ignored files fail with `SummError::AccessDenied` rather than being silently skipped. Path safety is enforced via `cpath::validate_rel` before any fs access.

`assemble_rollup_input` builds each rollup's prompt input by concatenating: `intent.md` (or `"(none)\n"` placeholder), then each child's `.ctx` content or, for subdirectories, their `rollup.ctx` — skipping `rollup.ctx` and `intent.md` themselves from the child listing to avoid duplication. Section labels and the `DIR_PATH:`/`--- intent.md ---` framing are part of the prompt contract with `summarizer-rollup.md`; changing the format here requires updating that prompt in sync.

`affected_dirs` computes the leaf-up traversal order via `cpath::ancestor_dirs` per target, deduped through a `BTreeSet`, then sorted by descending depth (repo root, `""`, always last). `scope_check(count, approve) -> Result<(), SummError>` is a pure guard against accidental large runs: rejects `count > MAX_TARGETS` (50) unless `approve` is true — callers must invoke it themselves, it isn't called internally by `run`.